cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of spectrally efficient operation of a multiuser uplink cognitive radio system in the presence of a single primary link. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes power allocation schemes and investigates the system's performance, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
